Sentencas: Developing new low-cost high-performance cobalt-free cathode materials for low temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs) has been an imperative topic.
Titulo: A novel in situ diffusion strategy to fabricate high performance cathodes for low temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In response to this challenge, we herein develop a novel in situ Pr diffusion strategy based on a Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta-Pr(Pr0.5Ba1.5)Cu3O7-delta (SDC-PBCu, 3 : 7 wt%) compound, to achieve a perovskite-related proton-blocking composite cathode (PBCC) Ce(1-x)PrxO(2-delta)-Ba2CeCu3O7.(4)-Sm2Ba1.33Ce0.67Cu3O9-CuO (PDC-BCC-SBCC-CuO) for BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta-based H-SOFCs.
Titulo: A novel in situ diffusion strategy to fabricate high performance cathodes for low temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell achieves a remarkable performance with a maximum power density (MPD) of 1000 and 566 mW cm(-2), corresponding to the interfacial polarization resistance (RP) of 0.037 and 0.188 Omega cm(2) at 700 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A novel in situ diffusion strategy to fabricate high performance cathodes for low temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The XRD results demonstrate that the PBCu phase disappears after the calcination of the mixed SDC-PBCu composite powder at 900 degrees C, with the formation of four new phases including fluorite structured PDC, orthorhombic layered material BCC, tetragonal perovskite-related SBCC and a small quantity of metallic oxide CuO, being favorable for a superior cathode performance.
Titulo: A novel in situ diffusion strategy to fabricate high performance cathodes for low temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ascendant electrochemical performance including the very high MPD and the lower R-P obtained here indicate that the quaternary cobalt-free PBCC PDC-BCC-SBCC-CuO is a preferable alternative for high-performance low-temperature H-SOFCs
Titulo: A novel in situ diffusion strategy to fabricate high performance cathodes for low temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
